32
00:02:16,679 --> 00:02:21,080
and native image is this ahead-of-time capability in GraalVM where we can take your application

33
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:24,600
and compile it ahead of time into a native executable.

34
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:29,479
And the reason to do so is because you will no longer need a JVM once you deploy the application,

35
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:32,000
it will be fully functional on its own.

36
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:37,440
And the reason to do so would be because you will eliminate many of the startup and resources

37
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:42,179
usage potential challenges that you can have with a larger Java application.

38
00:02:42,179 --> 00:02:46,160
So because we are optimizing and compiling your application ahead of time, we are doing

39
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:50,360
that work once and then you can start fast every single time.

40
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:53,559
So this is the startup, because you compile the application ahead of time, but there are

41
00:02:53,559 --> 00:02:57,639
also other benefits and ones that I would argue are more important than startup, one

42
00:02:57,639 --> 00:02:59,960
of such benefits is memory usage.

43
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:03,880
So if you want to run your application using less memory, on average about I would say

44
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:09,520
3x, 5x less than on the JVM, native image can do it for you because we no longer need

45
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:12,839
to load classes, interpret, compile, et cetera.

46
00:03:12,839 --> 00:03:18,039
So that's one benefit, startup memory usage, also you will get much more compact images

47
00:03:18,039 --> 00:03:23,399
and also native image gives you an additional security layer because there are way less

48
00:03:23,399 --> 00:03:28,039
dynamic features or they are restricted and only allowed by the allowed list.

49
00:03:28,039 --> 00:03:31,259
And also native image eliminates all the code that you are not using.

50
00:03:31,259 --> 00:03:35,960
So the idea is to compile the application once and then deploy it fast as many times

51
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,839
as you would need.

