00:10:26,299 --> 00:10:26,799
cetera.

148
00:10:26,799 --> 00:10:29,379
And the reason why this might be challenging for native image

149
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:31,539
is because native image compiles the application

150
00:10:31,539 --> 00:10:34,620
ahead of time under a closed world assumption.

151
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:37,060
And this means that runtime hasn't happened yet.

152
00:10:37,060 --> 00:10:39,460
So everything there is to know about your application

153
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:42,539
needs to be known when you build it.

154
00:10:42,539 --> 00:10:44,539
And this isn't a limitation of native image

155
00:10:44,539 --> 00:10:48,339
as much as it is a limitation of general AOT versus JIT.

156
00:10:48,339 --> 00:10:51,699
So you're compiling things ahead of time that need to be known.

157
00:10:51,699 --> 00:10:54,379
Now, native image can do pretty much anything for you

158
00:10:54,379 --> 00:10:56,859
as long as you tell it what exactly needs to be known

159
00:10:56,859 --> 00:10:59,019
and happening at build time.

160
00:10:59,179 --> 00:11:00,740
So how do you make reflection work,

